Free gingival grafts are important to increase zone of attached gingiva and root coverage.

 This case series reveals role of platelet-rich fibrin (PRF) as adjunctive therapy in palatal wound healing.

 The superior healing observed at the PRF membrane sites supports its use in accelerating soft-tissue healing.

 PRF membrane as a palatal bandage is an efficacious approach to protect the raw wound area of a palatal donor site to reduce healing time and patient discomfort.

